# Autonomous Campus Delivery Robot

## Simple Overview of the Project

This document presents the planning and implementation of an autonomous campus delivery robot aimed at addressing the logistical challenges created by the discontinuation of Sunway University's previous delivery system. The solution integrates SLAM technology with an efficient path planning approach and is developed on the ROS 1 platform, utilizing the pre-built HiWonder JetAuto hardware.

This project demonstrates the use of ROS-based SLAM on the JetAuto robot using the GMapping algorithm for autonomous mapping, while implementing TEB and Dijkstra algorithms for intelligent path planning. It supports autonomous navigation, real-time visualization in RViz, and persistent map storage for reliable campus delivery operations.

